What note?

32:27.318 --> 32:29.945
Oh, God,
I forgot to give you it.
Here. I still have it.

32:29.980 --> 32:32.519
Withholding evidence.
Not suspicious at all.

32:34.688 --> 32:35.753
"Mr. Locke"?

32:35.788 --> 32:37.425
My pen name. Ralph Locke.

32:37.460 --> 32:38.855
Sounds made up.

32:39.594 --> 32:40.791
It's a pen name.

32:42.465 --> 32:44.432
"Enjoy your stay."

32:44.467 --> 32:47.666
Yeah, Griz,
you better run that down
to forensics,<i> tout de suite.</i>

32:49.967 --> 32:53.111
Oh, are you Ferberizing?
Is that why you're tired?

32:53.146 --> 32:56.180
Yeah, yeah,
we are actually.
We're Ferberizing him.

32:57.480 --> 33:00.745
I never knew any creature
on earth could just cry so much.

33:00.780 --> 33:04.980
But it's gonna be so worth it
when Charlie can self soothe.
Cute!

33:05.015 --> 33:08.291
She's not wrong,
but you have to stick with it.

33:10.526 --> 33:13.164
You shook a police tail today.
You rented a fast car.

33:13.199 --> 33:15.265
Your fingerprints
are on the murder weapon,

33:15.300 --> 33:18.400
and someone matching
your description was seen
with the victim.

33:19.271 --> 33:20.534
I could arrest you.

33:20.569 --> 33:21.964
And we're not
going to arrest him?

33:21.999 --> 33:23.834
Who wants to do that paperwork?
Am I right?

33:25.442 --> 33:29.213
If you did it, Irwin,
I will catch you.

33:30.216 --> 33:32.040
I don't like people
calling me Irwin.

33:32.075 --> 33:34.746
Dang! Pigs have
crazy long orgasms!

34:12.291 --> 34:13.323
Hey!

34:21.564 --> 34:22.761
Hey!

34:22.796 --> 34:23.861
Fuck!

34:24.402 --> 34:25.665
Hey!

34:33.477 --> 34:35.642
Ow.

34:49.053 --> 34:50.591
-I'm here to--
-No.

34:51.264 --> 34:52.296
Yes.

34:53.497 --> 34:54.529
Okay.

34:55.059 --> 34:56.267
Bye.

34:56.302 --> 34:58.236
I'm here to see Frank Jaffe.

34:58.271 --> 35:00.931
Do you have a meeting?
No, just tell him
Fletch is here.

35:00.966 --> 35:02.768
Is that a first name
or a last name?

35:02.803 --> 35:04.176
Just Fletch.

35:04.211 --> 35:05.342
Just Fletch?

35:06.477 --> 35:07.608
Cool.

35:08.446 --> 35:11.282
Larry,
you let this prick in?

35:11.317 --> 35:13.152
Hi, Frank. Thank you.

35:14.815 --> 35:17.486
"Brown Out."
Septic tank explosion.

35:17.521 --> 35:18.751
I get it. Very clever.

35:18.786 --> 35:20.423
Did the Pulitzer committee
see this?

35:20.458 --> 35:21.952
Fuck you.
You still owe me money.

35:21.987 --> 35:23.294
What? No, I don't.

35:23.329 --> 35:25.230
Yes, you do.
For what?

35:25.265 --> 35:27.265
For charging a fuckload
of ridiculous shit
to the<i> News Tribune</i>

35:27.300 --> 35:28.992
and leaving town.
I had to pay for it.

35:29.027 --> 35:31.566
You rented
a fucking carriage horse.
Language.

35:33.130 --> 35:34.668
I paid you back.
No, you didn't.

35:34.703 --> 35:36.241
I apologized for
not paying you back.

35:36.276 --> 35:38.375
No, you didn't.
Well, I meant to.

35:38.410 --> 35:41.444
Listen, where is everybody?
They're still working
from home.

35:41.479 --> 35:43.446
Can you believe it?
The fucking babies.

35:43.481 --> 35:45.283
The place is like
a silent retreat.

35:45.318 --> 35:47.978
And these goddamn millennials,
they're so respectful.

35:48.013 --> 35:49.782
I can't tell you
how much I fucking hate
this place.

35:49.817 --> 35:51.322
You didn't bring anybody
from LA?

35:51.357 --> 35:53.115
Just Pete
who does The Jumble.

35:53.150 --> 35:54.325
Hey, Pete!

35:55.394 --> 35:56.525
Hey, Fletch.

35:57.088 --> 35:58.626
Jesus.

35:58.661 --> 36:00.694
I hate Pete too.
Mr. Excitement.

36:00.729 --> 36:02.025
What do you want,
Fletch?

36:02.060 --> 36:03.466
Can I talk to you
in your office?

36:03.501 --> 36:05.160
My office is
a fucking goldfish bowl.

36:05.195 --> 36:06.964
I can't even scratch
my nuts in there.

36:06.999 --> 36:09.032
Let's go to my real office.

36:09.067 --> 36:11.342
But you can't wear that hat.
They'll chop
your fucking head off.

36:14.677 --> 36:17.040
What brings you to Boston?

36:17.075 --> 36:18.976
'Cause if you're looking
for a job at a newspaper,
you're a fucking idiot,

36:19.011 --> 36:20.549
but I could use you.

36:20.584 --> 36:23.486
I have retired
from reporting.
Oh, good for you.

36:23.521 --> 36:29.723
Mmm. Do you happen to know
if luxury rental cars have
hidden GPS trackers in them?

36:29.758 --> 36:32.220
They do.
In case people steal them.
Why?

36:32.255 --> 36:35.564
Well, the police are
following me around.

36:35.599 --> 36:38.402
Oh, good. I hope
it's for something serious.
I need a pick me up.

36:38.437 --> 36:41.702
First night I'm here,
I get accused of murder.

36:43.068 --> 36:45.200
What?
Wait, the girl on the south end?

36:45.235 --> 36:47.202
That's the one, yes.

36:47.237 --> 36:50.238
Uh, you ever come across
this Detective Morris Monroe?

36:50.273 --> 36:52.009
He seems to think
that I'm the culprit.

36:52.044 --> 36:55.320
Really? Yeah, he's a smart guy.

36:56.389 --> 36:58.213
His father was a cop.
He's from Dorchester.

36:58.248 --> 37:00.017
Uh-- They call him
"Slow Mo Monroe",

37:00.052 --> 37:02.294
because he, uh, takes so long
to solve cases,

37:02.329 --> 37:04.725
but he solves a lot of cases.

37:04.760 --> 37:06.298
You think you could
pull some strings

37:06.333 --> 37:09.092
and, uh, find
a police report
on someone for me?

37:09.127 --> 37:12.194
No, Fletch. No way.
Way too big an ask.

37:13.263 --> 37:15.868
Oh. Just be a real shame
if Daphne found out

37:15.903 --> 37:19.773
that you defiled Clara Snow
in the supply closet
all those years ago.

37:19.808 --> 37:21.709
I mean, especially
in today's climate.

37:21.744 --> 37:24.107
-Mmm.
-You were her boss.

37:24.142 --> 37:27.946
First of all,
it wasn't the supply closet.
It was the copy room.

37:27.981 --> 37:30.388
And it was
a bilateral defiling.

37:31.820 --> 37:33.248
Are you really trying
to blackmail me?

37:34.119 --> 37:35.756
Kinda.

37:35.791 --> 37:37.923
-You wouldn't.
-No, you're probably right.

37:37.958 --> 37:41.124
On the other hand,
I am still under suspicion
for murder.

37:43.029 --> 37:46.371
Whose police report?
Owen Tasserly.

37:46.406 --> 37:47.471
Write it down,
you old lush.

37:49.002 --> 37:51.409
He was arrested a while back
for something.
I don't know what.

37:51.444 --> 37:53.774
But I think he might be
the actual murderer.

37:53.809 --> 37:55.204
I'll see what I can do.

37:55.976 --> 37:57.008
Thank you.

37:58.418 --> 38:01.683
But hey,
if you did kill that girl,
do the right thing.

38:02.620 --> 38:04.389
And give me an exclusive.

38:05.656 --> 38:07.282
Almost great seeing you again,
Frank.

38:08.285 --> 38:10.153
Just glad you kept
your fucking shoes on.

38:11.288 --> 38:13.530
Uh, hi,
is this Tatiana Tasserly?

38:14.566 --> 38:16.225
Yes, uh, it's Frank Jaffe.

38:16.260 --> 38:18.535
I'm the style editor
over at the<i> Boston Sentinel.</i>

38:18.570 --> 38:21.032
Listen, we were thinking
of doing a little piece

38:21.067 --> 38:23.408
on Boston's top
lifestyle curators

38:23.443 --> 38:25.872
and your name was
on the top of our list.

38:26.512 --> 38:27.544
I know.

38:29.009 --> 38:31.416
Well, that's just wonderful.
I would love to do that.

38:32.177 --> 38:34.815
I want a room to tell a story

38:34.850 --> 38:38.247
and all the pieces
are the characters.

38:38.282 --> 38:40.986
I wanna feel like
I'm in the middle
of a conversation.

38:41.021 --> 38:42.526
Between inanimate objects.
Right.

38:42.561 --> 38:45.122
Genius.
Oh, my gosh,
and this thing?

38:45.157 --> 38:48.730
Oh--
This idea of the branch
in the vase?

38:48.765 --> 38:50.930
I have--
How do you come up with this?

38:50.965 --> 38:53.603
-I-- I've only seen branches
on trees!
-Right. I know.

38:53.638 --> 38:55.000
I'm really giving it a moment,

38:55.035 --> 38:58.839
which lures the eye
to this gorgeous table.

38:58.874 --> 39:02.909
And I got this, Frank,
from a convent in Cuba.

39:02.944 --> 39:06.715
Wow. Those Cuban nuns
must be very proud.

39:06.750 --> 39:10.279
-Right?
-Even if they don't have
anywhere to eat anymore. Huh?

39:10.314 --> 39:13.183
Every single piece I curate
is bespoke.

39:13.218 --> 39:16.560
Ooh. Bespoke.
I love that word.

39:16.595 --> 39:17.660
What does it mean again?

39:17.695 --> 39:19.321
Bespoke?
Bespoke.

39:19.356 --> 39:24.568
-Uh, it's when
an object bespeaks. It...
-Right.

39:24.603 --> 39:25.998
...be-talks.

39:26.033 --> 39:27.571
It-- No, wait.

39:30.334 --> 39:35.513
It be-teaches us
something about ourselves.

39:37.407 --> 39:39.011
Wow. Thank you.
Yeah.

39:39.046 --> 39:40.947
I think I have my pull quote.

39:40.982 --> 39:44.720
I mean, so many people, Frank,
are trapped
in a world of sameness.

39:44.755 --> 39:49.384
I just want to surround them
with beautiful things.

39:49.419 --> 39:52.387
Beautiful clothes.
Beautiful food.

39:52.422 --> 39:55.126
Don't you just hate people
who are too poor
to afford beauty?

39:56.965 --> 39:58.833
Um...

39:58.868 --> 40:01.099
The worst.

40:02.267 --> 40:04.267
Well...

40:04.302 --> 40:07.237
Anyway, you're currently
separated from your husband,
Owen Tasserly.

40:07.272 --> 40:09.547
Yes. Yeah. Yeah.
Okay.

40:09.582 --> 40:12.209
Uh, now, is he still co-owner
of Chez Aesthetica?

40:13.751 --> 40:15.718
We had an evolved
and harmonious disuniting.

40:15.753 --> 40:17.918
And he decided
to leave the company.
Hmm.

40:17.953 --> 40:22.186
Now, I-- I'm sure you heard
of the unfortunate incident
at his townhouse.

40:22.221 --> 40:24.694
The-- The murdered woman.
Yikes.

40:24.729 --> 40:26.762
We've been reporting on it
in the paper.

40:27.765 --> 40:30.931
We were totally shocked,
of course, um...

40:30.966 --> 40:33.934
Well, Owen's been away
traveling in Europe.

40:33.969 --> 40:35.507
Right.
So...

40:37.500 --> 40:41.106
I'm always looking for ways
to actuate the senses, so--

40:41.141 --> 40:44.582
Yeah, of course,
but if I could just follow up.

40:44.617 --> 40:47.244
You would make me
kind of a hero
back at the office,

40:47.279 --> 40:49.213
if you could give me
any kind of clue

40:49.248 --> 40:51.787
as to who
might have committed
that murder.

40:51.822 --> 40:53.756
Frank, sorry,
I can't help you there.

40:53.791 --> 40:55.153
Um...

40:57.289 --> 40:58.728
But Owen can be
so irresponsible.

40:58.763 --> 41:00.488
So many people have keys
to that house.

41:00.523 --> 41:02.424
His housekeeper,
his trainer,

41:02.459 --> 41:06.032
his pothead neighbor
who feeds his fish,
and God knows who else.

41:07.431 --> 41:09.233
Why doesn't he
just change the lock?

41:09.268 --> 41:12.467
Frank, I have told him
a million times.

41:14.812 --> 41:17.208
Owen can be
such a fucking idiot sometimes.

41:17.243 --> 41:18.979
Hmm.

41:19.014 --> 41:21.982
I'm so happy you're here,
Frank. Such a fan.

41:40.365 --> 41:41.969
More water.
Your Negroni.

41:42.004 --> 41:44.235
<i>Oh, grazie. Grazie.</i>
Some olives.

41:49.682 --> 41:50.912
Ah, thank you.

41:51.409 --> 41:52.815
It's so nice.

41:52.850 --> 41:56.313
Ah, Fletch, you're late.

41:58.757 --> 42:00.053
Can I get you a drink?
Yes, please.

42:00.088 --> 42:02.022
A vodka gimlet.
Thank you very much.

42:02.057 --> 42:03.958
The staff seems
very smitten with you.

42:03.993 --> 42:07.896
Fletch, I am not going
to have any of your
American double-talk.

42:07.931 --> 42:10.701
I want truth.
Where are my paintings?

42:10.736 --> 42:13.462
Well, see,
here I thought they were
the Count's paintings.

42:13.497 --> 42:16.201
Oh, the Count is dead.

42:16.841 --> 42:18.203
How do you know this?

42:18.238 --> 42:21.140
I know in my heart.
The pain I feel.

42:22.880 --> 42:24.649
You and Angela think

42:24.684 --> 42:29.214
I was only with my Menti,
my<i> pequeno javali,</i>
for money,

42:29.249 --> 42:31.282
but this is lies.

42:31.317 --> 42:32.690
<i> Pequeno javali?</i>

42:32.725 --> 42:37.486
Mmm.
"Little boar" in Portuguese.

42:37.521 --> 42:41.699
I am half Brazilian,
also half Italian
and half French.

42:41.734 --> 42:43.998
That's, uh-- Huh.

42:44.033 --> 42:48.673
Uh-- And what is the Countess
doing here in Boston
in this very expensive hotel?

42:48.708 --> 42:49.740
Thank you very much.

42:49.775 --> 42:51.401
I come to stop you.

42:51.436 --> 42:56.109
I know that you
and Angela plan
to rob my paintings.

42:56.144 --> 42:58.210
Confess, Fletch.

42:58.245 --> 43:01.543
I'm sorry, how do I know
that, uh, you didn't take
the paintings?

43:01.578 --> 43:04.986
Or have the Count kidnapped
or murdered?

43:05.021 --> 43:09.056
I loved my Menti.
I would do nothing
to harm him.

43:09.091 --> 43:12.092
I did not steal
the paintings.

43:12.127 --> 43:15.095
Fletch, if I murder anyone,
I will murder you.

43:16.736 --> 43:20.529
Now, Fletch,
come up to my room.

43:20.564 --> 43:22.333
I have something to show you.

43:22.368 --> 43:24.335
Well, that's not gonna happen,
Your Highness.

43:24.370 --> 43:26.843
Fine. I go up
and come back to show you.

43:26.878 --> 43:28.977
Order me another drink.

43:29.012 --> 43:30.044
<i>Grazie.</i>

43:36.822 --> 43:37.854
Okay.

43:39.990 --> 43:42.287
Morris, I thought I'd stop by.

43:43.686 --> 43:46.654
I couldn't--
He just came here.

43:46.689 --> 43:49.129
You're enjoying this,
aren't you?
Very much so.

43:49.164 --> 43:51.835
It's quite satisfying.
What? No day care today?

43:51.870 --> 43:54.970
My wife had
a doctor's appointment.
My nanny is, um, indisposed.

43:55.005 --> 43:56.840
It's her support dog's birthday.

43:56.875 --> 43:59.238
Is that dog registered anywhere?
I'd love to send it something.

43:59.273 --> 44:00.668
Okay, look,
are you here to confess?

44:00.703 --> 44:02.846
No, but I did have some ideas
about the case.

44:02.881 --> 44:05.475
Goddamn it! We are not
working on this case together,
Irwin.

44:08.513 --> 44:11.547
Come on, just hear me out.
What is happening?

44:12.154 --> 44:14.352
What?

44:14.387 --> 44:16.024
Hands can parade around naked
all day,

44:16.059 --> 44:17.894
but God forbid
you show a few toes?

44:17.929 --> 44:19.588
Now, come on.
Let's talk about
the suspects here.

44:19.623 --> 44:22.690
Number one.
Tatiana Tasserly,
Owen's ex-wife.

44:22.725 --> 44:25.132
-Who you dropped in on today.
-Yes, I did.

44:25.167 --> 44:28.168
Maybe she didn't know
Owen was out of town,
and she wanted to frame him.

44:28.203 --> 44:30.434
-Why?
-Acrimonious divorce.

44:30.469 --> 44:32.744
She wants control
over the company
that they share

44:32.779 --> 44:34.207
and custody of their daughter.

44:34.242 --> 44:36.781
Tatiana Tasserly
was in yoga class that night.

44:36.816 --> 44:38.211
Vinyasa or Bikram?

44:39.544 --> 44:41.016
We'll get back to that.

44:41.051 --> 44:43.282
She could have hired somebody
to do the job.

44:43.317 --> 44:45.515
Second, Eve, the neighbor.

44:45.550 --> 44:47.616
She has a key
to Owen's townhouse,

44:47.651 --> 44:49.684
she feeds his fish
while he's out of town

44:49.719 --> 44:53.061
and just happens
to be in love with him.
She admitted it to me.

44:53.096 --> 44:57.032
O-Okay. Okay.
W-What you're doing right now,
that's called witness tampering.

44:57.067 --> 44:59.067
You're just begging me
to arrest you.

44:59.102 --> 45:02.400
Come on, Morris.
You want me on the outside,
so I can solve this thing,

45:02.435 --> 45:04.138
-and then you can take
the credit.

45:06.538 --> 45:09.946
It's okay,
look at the cow.
Look at Mr. Moo. Mr. Moo.

45:09.981 --> 45:12.674
Daddy's got to talk
to the murderer right now.

45:12.709 --> 45:14.544
The only reason
I haven't arrested you yet

45:14.579 --> 45:17.789
is because I enjoy
watching you dig a deeper hole
for yourself.

45:17.824 --> 45:20.957
Eve has a motive.
Rejection, jealousy.

45:20.992 --> 45:23.190
I hope it's not Eve though.
I really like her.

45:23.225 --> 45:24.488
Such compassion.

45:24.523 --> 45:27.458
And then, of course,
Tasserly himself.

45:27.493 --> 45:29.768
I mean, it is his townhouse.

45:32.399 --> 45:35.532
Tasserly was on a flight
to Paris at- 27 p.m.
that night.

45:35.567 --> 45:38.172
Plenty of time to do a murder
before you get on that plane.

45:38.207 --> 45:39.943
Coroner has time of death
at- 00 p.m.

45:39.978 --> 45:41.571
You're gonna trust a coroner?
They're weirdos.

45:41.606 --> 45:43.243
Tasserly's motive?

45:43.278 --> 45:44.816
He's been a lunatic
since his wife left him.

45:44.851 --> 45:47.379
Oh, and someone
broke into his house
last night.

45:47.414 --> 45:49.986
I don't know who it was.
Couldn't get a good look,
but he had a beard.

45:50.021 --> 45:52.615
Might have been Tasserly.
He might be back in town.

45:52.650 --> 45:54.485
Owen Tasserly broke into
his own house?

45:56.489 --> 45:58.093
-Criminal mastermind.

45:58.128 --> 46:00.557
Whoever it was
did not want to get caught.

46:00.592 --> 46:03.131
He take anything?
Not that I could tell.

46:03.166 --> 46:04.198
Lakers fan?

46:05.102 --> 46:06.937
What do you think?
What about you?

46:08.204 --> 46:10.237
-What do you think?

46:10.272 --> 46:12.470
Charlie, Charlie--
Charlie, I get it.

46:12.505 --> 46:14.670
I'd be crying too
if I was a Celtics fan.

46:15.673 --> 46:17.178
Person of interest
leaving the building.

46:18.181 --> 46:20.049
Slow Mo, he's getting away!

46:20.084 --> 46:22.315
Watch it, pal.
He'll arrest you
at your retirement dinner.

46:22.350 --> 46:25.219
Hey, guy, don't worry.
Monroe's not even sure
who shot Lincoln.

46:27.355 --> 46:29.586
Somebody solve a crime.
How about that?

46:31.964 --> 46:33.326
Can you just--

46:33.361 --> 46:35.163
Oh, thank you. Go ahead.
After you.
Okay.

46:37.530 --> 46:38.661
Are you--

46:39.796 --> 46:41.367
Uh-- Uh, are we going up?

46:42.007 --> 46:43.039
God bless her.

47:04.557 --> 47:05.589
Hmm.

47:32.519 --> 47:34.189
Oh, he's on the move.

47:34.224 --> 47:36.389
If he crosses the state line,
I want to see where he goes.

47:36.424 --> 47:37.720
Hey, you coming?
No.

47:37.755 --> 47:39.854
"No." Love that.

47:39.889 --> 47:44.265
<i>Hummingbirds have a metabolism</i>
<i>77 times faster than ours.</i>

47:44.300 --> 47:47.433
<i>I got a hybrid diet craze</i>
<i>that's just around the corner.</i>

48:31.875 --> 48:33.545
Mr. Horan. How are you?

48:33.580 --> 48:35.349
-I'm well, thank you.
-Here for the clambake?

48:35.384 --> 48:37.351
No, I'm just here
to pick up some things
from the boat.

48:37.386 --> 48:40.189
I actually--
I can't have anything.
I'm allergic to shellfish.

48:40.224 --> 48:41.619
Are you?
Good to see you, Marv.

48:41.654 --> 48:43.918
But I can have corn--
Okay, bye.
Thank you.

48:49.134 --> 48:52.201
I'm allergic to shellfish,
so I can't really have--
Yeah, no.

48:52.236 --> 48:53.928
Okay. Well, see you.

48:53.963 --> 48:56.271
Come on in, Jack.
